description.narrative:
During these three years of implementation, AWEN has been an increasingly important actor in the women human rights field, concerning multiple components of women’s rights area, like protection of vulnerable women through different services offered by AWEN member organizations; awareness raising at national and local level of the wide public on women human rights; promotion of positive models of success; lobbying and advocacy for the rights of DV & trafficking victims in several areas (services, housing, employment, etc) through inputs at several draft laws and strategies, research based sensitization on intimate partner violence among adolescence, role of media in shaping mindsets on women human rights, etc. Furthermore, AWEN has further consolidated its image and role as an important civil society actor in women’s rights protection and promotion. Collaboration and interaction has been intensified with International entities as well as with central and local public institutions. At large, AWEN as a network organization has increasingly served as a forum for experience sharing, platform for advocacy and a legitimate “hub” for capacity development of it member organizations.
Indicators of this achievments are the following: 
- 1288 girls and women have been directly assisted for 2018; 1880 girls and women have been directly assisted for 2017 (1265 have been assisted during 2016); Total for 2016-2018: 4433 girls and women
- About 4415 girls and women during 2018 have received online/phone counseling/ assistance and referral to other services 2881 during 2017, 1132 during 2016; Total for 2016-2018: 8428 girls and women
- At least 5261 people (women and girls, boys and men) are more aware on women rights by participating in awareness raising events/activities of AWEN and AWEN member organizations during 2018; 4946 for 2017 and 3712 during 2016; Total for 2016-2018: 13919 girls and women?
- Around 400.000 people outreached though media events, public outreach national campaigns (estimated value – by AWEN and members during 2016-2018; 
- About 780 young girls and boys have been engaged as activists/ volunteers beside AWEN & its member organizations during 2018; 229 during 2017. Total for 2016-2018: 1009 girls and boys
- At least 29 perpetrators have benefitted from rehabilitation services (mainly psychological support); 19 during 2017. Total for 2016-2018 : 48 perpetrators.
- At least 654 local stakeholders have been involved during 2018, 1194 local stakeholders have been involved during 2017, by AWEN and member organizations (641 during 2016);
- A new emergency shelter’ opening has been supported in Dibra district;
- Nine (9) Referral Mechanisms have been supported during 2016-2018; 4 new Referral Mechanisms’ establishment have been supported by member organization;
